name: Gallon House Sunset
description:
Title: Gallon House Sunset
Location: Mount Angel, Oregon
Year Taken: 2021
About this photo: Drones are amazing tools. This is a view that is not only unseeable by average photographers due to the elevation, but it is taken from the side of a covered bridge known as the Gallon House Bridge. Named from the remnants of the prohibition era, moonshine and other contraband were sold and exchanged near the Gallon House Bridge, located on a country road just outside of Mount Angel and Silverton, Oregon. Fitting, then, that a couple was sitting in their car smoking marijuana.
